Looping in programming languages is a feature which facilitates the execution of a set of instructions/functions repeatedly
while some condition evaluates to true. Java provides three ways for executing the loops.
While all the ways provide similar basic functionality, they differ in their syntax and condition checking time.


There're FOUR Types of Basics.Loops in JAVA
1) While Loop
2) For Loop
3) ForEach Loop / Enhanced For Loop
4) Do-While Loop

